Tableau Accelerators for Data Cloud

A Tableau accelerator provides ready-to-use dashboards and workbooks geared for a particular industry or business use case. All Tableau accelerators use the Salesforce Data Cloud connector to connect Tableau and Data Cloud.

Data Cloud Identity Resolution Accelerator

Explore how identity resolution in Data Cloud is working for your business. In Tableau, view your ingested sources, how they contribute to unified individuals, and their composition. See how matching rules and data quality affect your identity resolution results.

See Data Cloud Identity Resolution on Tableau Exchange and on Salesforce AppExchange.

Data Cloud Email Marketing Campaign Accelerator

Get a jump-start to data-driven insights in Tableau for monitoring the efficiency of your email campaigns. Explore campaigns that have the highest conversion, check email trends over time, and more.

See Data Cloud Email Marketing Campaign on Tableau Exchange and on Salesforce AppExchange.

Data Cloud Customer Engagement Accelerator

Provide an exploratory Tableau dashboard to give marketing and sales teams with a comprehensive view of the engagement levels of customers across these channels:

Sales
Email
Messages (SMS)
Website
Push Notifications

Select the best channels to interact with a customer, develop relevant messaging, and create positive experiences to increase loyalty and retention.

See Data Cloud Customer Engagement on Tableau Exchange and on Salesforce AppExchange.

Data Cloud Sales Accelerator

Assess and improve your sales performance by combining sales and customer data together in a single view with data from multiple Salesforce orgs or business units. The data is ingested and harmonized into Data Cloud, which unifies sales data to analyze in Tableau.

See Data Cloud Sales on Tableau Exchange and on Salesforce AppExchange.

Data Cloud Sales Pipeline Accelerator

Analyze your business in a single view using opportunity data from multiple Salesforce orgs or business units. The data is ingested and harmonized into Data Cloud, which unifies opportunities pipeline data and the overall sales pipeline to analyze in Tableau.

See Data Cloud Sales Pipeline on Tableau Exchange and on Salesforce AppExchange.

Data Cloud Weighted Sales Pipeline Accelerator

Get a more accurate and realistic analysis of pipeline opportunity data based on the probability of closing. This accelerator brings opportunity data from multiple Salesforce orgs or business units into a single view. Compared to standard Pipeline, the Weighted Pipeline introduces the concept of "Probability of Closing" (expressed in %) for each opportunity, which provides a more accurate and realistic analysis of the pipeline to explore in Tableau.

See Data Cloud Weighted Sales Pipeline on Tableau Exchange and on Salesforce AppExchange.

Data Cloud Service Desk Accelerator

Make better business decisions, influence Key Performance Indicators (KPI), and improve overall customer service by bringing in data from multiple Salesforce orgs or business units. The data is ingested and harmonized into Data Cloud. View data across your entire business, including across individual Service Cloud instances in Tableau. From there, you can drill down to individual business units, all the way down to individual service agents.

See Data Cloud Service Desk Accelerator on Tableau Exchange and on Salesforce AppExchange.

Data Cloud Retail Sales Accelerator

Unlock sales and product performance across different store locations by bringing in data from multiple Salesforce orgs or business units. The data is ingested and harmonized into Data Cloud and represented in a single view in Tableau. You can analyze overall sales across all your orgs or business units as well as drill down to the lowest level of detail: Store Location, Product Line, and Product.

See Data Cloud Retail Sales on Tableau Exchange and on Salesforce AppExchange.

Data Cloud Sales vs Quota Accelerator

Explore your sales performance results versus quota across your sales teams and products or services by bringing in data from multiple Salesforce orgs or business units. The data is ingested and harmonized into Data Cloud, which is then assessed in Tableau to effectively appraise your sales performance from different perspectives: Month-to-Date, Year-to-Date, and Actual vs Quota vs LY.

See Data Cloud Sales vs Quota on Tableau Exchange and on Salesforce AppExchange.

NOTE If you experience an issue when using an accelerator, share the details with your Tableau Account Team and ask them to contact the Tableau Accelerator Team to review the issue. Salesforce Support doesn’t support the Tableau accelerators for Data Cloud available on Tableau Exchange and Salesforce AppExchange.
